result.execSummary:
The defendant Alexander K Rankin was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Child Enticement-Sexual Contact, a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.07(1).
  • Attempt 2nd Degree Sexual Assault of Child, a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.02(2).
  • Soliciting a Child for Prostitution [Modifiers: Conspiracy to Commit], a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.08.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. charges.descr: Use a Computer to Facilitate a Child Sex Crime

supervisions.notes: Consecutive to any other sentence but concurrent on all counts.  Defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  Defendant IS NOT eligible for the Substance Abuse Program
Conditions of Extended Supervision shall be the same as conditions of probation.

miscConds.notes: BOND APPLIED.  COSTS PAID IN FULL.

No use or possession of any computer, hard drive, external storing device, smart phone or other digital media without prior approval of agent.
  
No access to the internet  without prior agent approval.

No contact with any person under the age of 18 unless approved by the agent.

Complete compas assessment,  counseling, evaluations, programs and assessments as appropriate and followup.  Pay supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections and follow rules of supervision.  Defendant shall provide a DNA sample by calling the Work Release Unit  at 920-232-1915 or 920-232-1919 WITHIN 72 HOURS OF SENTENCING to set up an appointment.   The Work Release Units hours are 8:00 am-4:00 pm/Monday thru Friday. Defendant shall provide proof of identification along with the court minutes stating a DNA sample is required.  Failure to comply with this order may result in either a finding of contempt of court or a criminal charge of Failure to Provide a DNA Sample pursuant to Wis. Stats. 946.52.


Must comply with the Sex Offender Registry for the term of supervision followed by 15 years after discharge.  
The defendant shall participate and follow any and all recommendations by the department regarding assessments and treatment which may include Sex Offender Treatment programming, AODA, Psychological, and any cognitive intervention as directed by the agent.  
Comply with Sex Offender Registry Program under 301.45, Wis. Stats.

timeConds.notes:
On each count concurrent.  NO good time.  Huber granted, if in compliance with jail facility regulations.  Defendant shall report to the Work Release Unit (M-F/7:30 am to 3:30 pm), within 72 hours of sentence date with a copy of the minute sheet and the completed GPS application to establish report date for serving sentence.  Report date shall be within 60 days of sentence date.  Huber shall be revoked for failure to report and a warrant shall be authorized.
Court authorizes transfer to Walworth County.
IMPOSED & STAYED - Stay may be lifted, in whole or in part, upon written request of the agent with approval and order of the court.
